    "reasoning": "The initial input_spec described a module with clk, reset, w and z. However, the golden testbench includes a stimulus_gen with clk, reset, w, and tb with clk, reset, w, z_dut, z_ref. The testbench code follows the golden testbench which contradicts the input_spec's mention of w as input. Hence, the module's ports must match the golden testbench: clk, reset (input), w (input), z (output). The testbench's MAX_QUEUE_SIZE is set to 10, and queues are of size 10. The display on mismatch shows time, stored signals from clk, reset, w, z, and expected z_ref. After simulation, if no errors, display simulation passed; else, failed message with count and first time. The golden testbench's error detection uses 'tb_match' derived from comparing z and z_ref. The testbench's initial stimulus generation in stimulus_gen uses non-blocking assignments, repeated for 200 cycles. The TopModule's state machine is implemented with states like A, B, C, etc., with transitions based on the described FSM. State assignments and sequential logic are handled in separate always blocks. Outputs z are assigned via continuous assignment based on current state and input.",
    "interface": "module TopModule (input logic clk, input logic reset, input logic w, output logic z);",
    "testbench": "`timescale 1ps/1ps\nmodule tb();\n    reg clk = 0;\n    reg reset;\n    reg w;\n    wire z;\n    // Clock generation\n    always #5 clk = ~clk;\n\n    stimulus_gen stim (\n        .clk(clk),\n        .reset(reset),\n        .w(w)\n    );\n\n    TopModule dut (\n        .clk(clk),\n        .reset(reset),\n        .w(w),\n        .z(z)\n    );\n\n    logic z_ref;\n    RefModule ref (\n        .clk(clk),\n        .reset(reset),\n        .w(w),\n        .z(z_ref)\n    );\n\n    // Queue management for error tracking\n    reg [1:0] clk_queue [0:9];\n    reg [1:0] reset_queue [0:9];\n    reg [1:0] w_queue [0:9];\n    reg [1:0] z_queue [0:9];\n    reg [1:0] z_ref_queue [0:9];\n    integer queue_ptr = 0;\n    integer error_count = 0;\n    integer error_time = 0;\n\n    // Mismatch detection\n    always @(negedge clk) begin\n        if (z !== z_ref) begin\n            if (error_count == 0) begin\n                error_time = $time;\n            end\n            error_count += 1;\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Simulation timeout after 100000\n    initial begin\n        #100000 $finish;\n    end\n\n    // Simulation end display\n    initial begin\n        wait(error_count > 0);\n        if (error_count == 0) begin\n            $display(\"SIMULATION PASSED\");\n        end else begin\n            $display(\"SIMULATION FAILED - %0d MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME %0d\", error_count, error_time);\n            // Display queue\n            $display(\"Last 10 cycles of simulation: \");\n            for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) begin\n                $display(\"Cycle %0d: clk=%b, reset=%b, w=%b, z=%b, z_ref=%b\", i, clk_queue[i], reset_queue[i], w_queue[i], z_queue[i], z_ref_queue[i]);\n            end\n        end\n        $finish;\n    end\nendmodule\n\nmodule stimulus_gen (\n    input clk,\n    output logic reset,\n    output logic w\n);\n    initial begin\n        reset = 0;\n        w = 0;\n        repeat(200) @(negedge clk) begin\n            reset <= ($r